  "instructions": {
    "text_instructions": [
      {
        "id": "01f10ccb12b91396805e8a6e74971707",
        "content": [
          "You must ONLY return two columns in your final output: Segment Details and Examples. Do not include counts, percentages, or other columns unless explicitly asked for a visualization.\r\n",
          "\r\n",
          "The Examples column must contain exactly 5 GCID values per segment by default. Use the logic slice(collect_list(GCID), 1, 5).\r\n",
          "\r\n",
          "Segmentation Defaults:\r\n",
          "\r\n",
          "If a user asks for \"segmentation\" without specifying a field, always use CustomerAge as the default dimension.\r\n",
          "\r\n",
          "By default, divide the data into 5 segments using NTILE(5) or WIDTH_BUCKET.\r\n",
          "\r\n",
          "If the user asks for \"Germany\" or any country, filter by the Country column before segmenting.\r\n",
          "\r\n",
          "Business Logic:\r\n",
          "\r\n",
          "Always exclude users where IsExcludeUser is True.\r\n",
          "\r\n",
          "When segmenting by CustomerAge, the Segment Details column should describe the age range (e.g., \"Age Group 1: 18-25\").\r\n",
          "\r\n",
          "FirstTimeDeposit_Date is the source of truth for \"Depositing\" or \"FTD\" users."
        ]
      }
    ],
